First Lady Michelle Obama will be delivering remarks at a White House screening of the film Hidden Figures on Thursday, December 15th. The event will feature cast members Kevin Costner, Taraji P. Henson, Janelle Monae, and Octavia Spencer, and will highlight the stories of Americans who have made significant contributions in the history of space flight, space science, and innovation. Hidden Figures is a biographical film that tells the story of NASA pioneers Katherine Johnson, Dorothy Vaughn, and Mary Jackson, who enabled the first launches of Americans into space.